headline.main: BRITISH HAMMER NAZI ARCTIC LINE; Bombers of Fleet Arm and the R.A.F. Blast Supply Vessels in Norwegian Fjords FIGHT ENEMY'S WARSHIPS Offensive Over Strait of Dover Pressed by Other Squadrons Through Day and Night

lead_paragraph: LONDON, Saturday, Oct. 11 -- Blows struck by aircraft of the British Navy and the Royal Air Force against the Germans' northern lines of communication toward Russia along the coast of Norway were recounted yesterday.
abstract: Brit blast German supply ships in Norwegian fjords
